From: quark <quark@localhost>
Subject: [PATCH] kernelbase: Substitute calling process PID for magic Steam PID 0xfffe

Steam's steam.exe helper writes PID 0xfffe to the registry at
HKCU\Software\Valve\Steam\ActiveProcess\PID. Games read this and call
OpenProcess(0xfffe) to verify Steam is alive. Since we run our own
steam.exe builtin (not the Windows Steam client), substitute the
caller's own PID so the check succeeds.

Ported from wine-valve (Proton).

--- a/dlls/kernelbase/process.c
+++ b/dlls/kernelbase/process.c
@@ -1104,6 +1104,9 @@

     InitializeObjectAttributes( &attr, NULL, inherit ? OBJ_INHERIT : 0, 0, NULL );

+    /* Steam ActiveProcess registry PID hack: games query 0xfffe to check if Steam is alive. */
+    if (id == 0xfffe) id = GetCurrentProcessId();
+
     cid.UniqueProcess = ULongToHandle(id);
     cid.UniqueThread  = 0;

